  "description": "Continuing juvenile bird that has been in the area for weeks. This bird was on a snag to the south of the island where most of the other DCCOs and CAGU were located. Next to it was a DCCO, so the size comparison was easy to see. 30% smaller than nearby adult DCCO. Proportionally longer tail than several nearby DCCOs. Uniformly brownish neck without the light color of a nearby Juvenile DCCO on the island. Faint outline of triangular-shaped gape extending to rear of eye. Can be seen in photo. No color above eye.",
